description:
Job responsibilities:
Design web pages for corporate branding and work on interface solutions
Support senior designers to create and convey design solutions
Analysis and improvement for the design projects (wireframe, mockup and prototype)
Design for the advertising material and relevant graphics when needed
Handle ad-hoc tasks or projects as assigned
Requirements:
Higher Diploma or Degree in Web Design/ Graphic Design or related discipline;
At least 2 years working experience in Website/ Graphic Design/ UI/UX work, with experience of a full cycle project in mobile/web;
Current experience in web design, digital promotion, graphic design with promotion material etc;
Solid experience in designing Corporate Branding / commercial website/marketing material etc;
Proficient in Adobe Creative, Photoshop, Illustrator, XD etc;
A portfolio to demonstrate design work;
Work independently and good team player;
Good in spoken and writing in English and Chinese
Please click "Apply Now" to submit your application.


Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Responsibilities:

Take work from concept to final execution within deadline;
Understand marketing initiatives, strategic positioning and target audience; 
Communicate with clients & sales team in order to ensure the design meet customers' requirements;
Carry out graphic design and artwork production for printing Annual Report purposes as assigned; and
Perform digital design works including but not limited to design website’s visual imagery, graphics, animations and production of relevant digital photographs.

Job Requirements:

Design institute graduate or above;
5 years or above solid experience in graphic/ digital design field; 
Experience in the implementation of mobile/ responsive web layouts design would be advantageous;
Proficient in Adobe InDesign, Illustrator and Photoshop, MS Office;
Good command of both spoken Mandarin & Cantonese;
Self-motivated, responsible and detail-oriented;
A good teamwork player; and
Candidate with more experience will be considered for the position of  Assistant Art Director.

We offer competitive remuneration package. Interested parties please send full resume including date of availability, current and expected salary to HR Department, 2/F, 100QRC, 100 Queen’s Road Central, Hong Kong or by fax to 2523 7232 or by clicking apply now.

To understand more about EQUITY GROUP, please visit our website at http://www.equitygroup.com.hk

Data collected is for recruitment purpose only.

Job Highlights

Website and mobile app user interface designs
Graphic and digital design for banner
Work with project and development team

Job Responsibilities

Website and mobile app user interface designs;
Produce all kind of graphic and digital design for banner and other presentation materials;
Work with project and development team; and
Manage any ad-hoc tasks or projects as assigned.

Job Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in digital design, multimedia design, graphic communications or related field;
Minimum 1 years' of working experience in design related field
Hands on skills in Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, Sketch;
Knowledge of UI design principles and techniques;
Detail minded with can-do attitude and ability to multitask;
Provide online portfolio link in addition to resume. *Immediate availability is preferred

Working location & hours

5-days work
Work in Kwun Tong

Casetify is looking for a Senior UXUI designer experienced in information architecture, interaction, and user testing to join our team. You will collaborate with the E-commerce team to design and build next generation Web/mobile applications. The right candidates will be excellent communicators, comfortable in a high-velocity startup, and passionate about creating products that transform people’s lifestyle.
Responsibilities:
Prepare UX/UI design and materials including wire framing, mockup and rapid prototyping for various interfaces, including websites, mobile devices and apps for ecommerce site;
Analyze current user journey to understand motivation, expose pain points, issues and improvement opportunities;
Conduct user research, A/B testing, and propose solutions to optimize customer experience;
Communicate concepts and work collaboratively with project team / Tech team in order to develop the most efficient design schemas;
Sit with developers to do pixel-perfect reviews of frontend products before they are pushed in production;
Consume our Design System library and contribute to its evolution.
Requirements:


Bachelor Degree in Creative Media / Interactive Design / Web Design / Web Development;
5+ years of experience building transactional website;
Specific experience in a fast growing ecommerce company;
Ability to solve problems of complexity through smart design;
Being data-driven, and be able to back up your assertions with data, with proficiency in analytic tools - Hotjar, Google Analytics, Optimizely etc;
A user-first attitude and ensure we consistently deliver a user-centric culture;
Strong understanding of web grids and browser limitations;
Familiarity with usability testing, A/B testing methods;
Proficiency with Photoshop, Adobe XD, Webflow, HTML, CSS, PHP;
Bouns: Experience with Shopify site designs / SDK.
Please include 2 URLs of your Open Source, personal projects into your resume.

Job Requirements:
Diploma/University degree in advertising, graphic design or a relevant discipline;
Solid working experience in graphic design and advertising with knowledge in web building, CSS, CMS and HTML 5 preferred;
Familiar with current graphic design practice, such as Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe In Design and Flash;
Excellent communication skills with good command in written & spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Able to handle multiple tasks of varying complexities within deadlines;
Able to work well under pressure
Fresh graduates are welcome to apply
Key Job Responsibilities:
To create superior and original designs for the school website and promotional materials include posters, flyers, logos, banners, signage, etc.
To liaise with external agencies such as printing houses, web developers and AD agencies
To work with marketing team on promotional projects and to help in executing marketing activities such as delivery of presentations and promotions at education exhibitions in Hong Kong, Macau or Mainland China
To communicate with parents, students and prospective parties about our school programs
We offer 5-day work to the right candidates. Interested parties please send your full resume with date available and expected salary to Human Resources Office via email by clicking "Apply Now".
Closing Date:  January 20, 2022
(Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

To cope with the departmental growth, we are looking for a creative graphic designer to join our Hong Kong office. The ideal candidate should have graphics and multimedia design background, a good sense of aesthetics, good communication skills, willingness to undertake a wide range of tasks and will work in a team as well as individually.

Responsibilities:

Provide innovative ideas for web development and motion graphic design;
Assist in video shooting and editing;
Responsible for photo shooting and retouch of event/product shot;
Produce multimedia materials, such as web banner, eDM, posters and other electronic promotion materials;
Develop artwork design and website visual content.

Requirements:

Higher diploma or above in Multimedia/Graphic Design or other related disciplines;
Minimum 1 year experience in video editing, shooting & multimedia;
Knowledge in sound editing and graphic design tools, such as After Effects, Premiere, GarageBand, Illustrator, Photoshop, Adobe CS5 Suite, etc.;
Knowledge of 3D software, such as Maya, 3Ds Max, etc.;
Familiar with Search Engine Optimization, eDM design and eCommerce technologies will be an advantage;
Self-motivated, able to work under pressure and quality oriented;
Good command of written and spoken English;
Fresh graduates with potential will also be considered



We offer an attractive remuneration package including 5-day work, flexible work hours and other benefits to the right candidates. Interested parties please forward full resume with expected salary and quote job reference number by "Apply Now" or to

VTech Group of Companies,
The Human Resources and Administration Department,
23/F, Block 1, Tai Ping Industrial Centre,
57 Ting Kok Road, Tai Po, Hong Kong

For more information about us, please visit our website at: www.vtech.com   

All applications will be used for the purpose of recruitment only. Applicants not invited for an interview within 4 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful. We will retain the applications for a maximum period of six months and may refer them to suitable openings within our Group.

